(- Subsidy is clipped at coinbase by remaining cap headroom.) Tj
T*
(- After cap is reached, subsidy remains 0 and fees continue through the same burn/pool paths.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Fee and Burn Math) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Per block at full utilization) Tj
T*
(- Total fee capacity at floor: 3,500,000 * 500 = 1,750,000,000 atoms = 1.75 ATHO) Tj
T*
(- Routed-to-pool share at tail \(55%\): 0.9625 ATHO) Tj
T*
(- Burn-path share at tail \(45%\): 0.7875 ATHO) Tj
T*
(- Tail issuance per block: 0.1953125 ATHO) Tj
T*
(- Net per-block formula: Delta_block = 0.1953125 - \(0.7875 * utilization\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Per year at full utilization) Tj
T*
(- Tail issuance: 0.1953125 * 262,800 = 51,328.125 ATHO/year) Tj
T*
(- Total annual fees at floor: 459,900 ATHO/year) Tj
T*
(- Annual burn-path max \(45%\): 206,955 ATHO/year) Tj
T*
(- Annual net formula: Delta_year = 51,328.125 - \(206,955 * utilization\)) Tj
T*
(- Formula above applies while subsidy is still positive; after hard-cap clip, subsidy term is 0.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Deflation Threshold) Tj
T*
(Set annual net to zero:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(51,328.125 - 206,955u = 0) Tj
T*
(u = 51,328.125 / 206,955 ~= 0.24802) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(So:) Tj
T*
(- <24.802%: inflationary protocol net.) Tj
T*
(- =24.802%: neutral.) Tj
T*
(- >24.802%: deflationary protocol net \(until floor clipping binds\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
