T*
(Floor-Clipped Burn Behavior) Tj
T*
(Burn is constrained by available headroom:) Tj
T*
(- burn_headroom = emitted_up_to - cumulative_burned_before - supply_floor) Tj
T*
(- effective_burn = min\(desired_burn, routed_non_pool_fees, burn_headroom\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Implications:) Tj
T*
(- Consensus cannot burn below 21,000,000 ATHO effective circulating supply.) Tj
T*
(- At/near floor, burn is clipped to available headroom.) Tj
T*
(- Unburned routed fees fall through to miner accounting for exact coinbase closure.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bottom Line) Tj
T*
(Atho?s active model is:) Tj
T*
(- **400M total pre-tail base over ~64.69 years** \(399.21875M subsidy + 781,250 bootstrap\),) Tj
T*
(- then fixed tail subsidy \(0.1953125 ATHO/block\) until clipped by hard-cap headroom,) Tj
T*
(- with pool-routed fees and burn on routed non-pool share,) Tj
T*
(- with a hard max emitted supply cap of **500,000,000 ATHO**,) Tj
T*
(- and a hard **21M supply floor**.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Current utilization pivot is **~24.802%** for neutral net supply change.) Tj
T*
